YELLOWBUD SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Yellowbud Solar, LLC ("Yellowbud") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Yellowbud generating facility ("Yellowbud Facility").
Yellowbud is a solar generating facility located in Ross and Pickaway Counties, Ohio. The Yellowbud Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities within the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") region.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Yellowbud's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Yellowbud Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Yellowbud's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Yellowbud shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $3,068,912.43 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $255,742.70
